<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09176</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT CREATING THE DEPARTMENT OF WATER, IRRIGATION, SEWAGE, FLOOD CONTROL, AND SANITATION RESOURCE MANAGEMENT, DEFINING ITS POWERS AND FUNCTIONS, APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to improve our waters by:  ensuring and improving the country's sustainable community-based water sources; protection of watersheds and water sources; lending program to Local Water Districts; sewage and sanitation resource management; as well as flood control and flood risk management.

Seeks to better manage the entire cycle of our water - from sourcing to water treatment and sewage to achieve more sustainable water supply and better overall management of our irrigation, sanitation, flood management, and sewage.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>CUA, DAKILA CARLO E.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-04-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-05-20</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON PUBLIC WORKS AND HIGHWAYS</td></tr></table>